The footage, circulating on social media shows equipment, including coastal defence systems heading towards Helsinki, just days after Finlands websites were the target of a cyber attack. Finland has previously avoided joining the military alliance but the war in Ukraine has sparked a reconsideration. Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov warned both Finland and Sweden against NATO membership saying "the alliance remains a tool geared towards confrontation" and further expansion would not bring stability to Europe. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...